# A concise description of what this element means (e.g. for use in autogenerated summaries).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Condition.code.coding:SCT/short
msgid "SNOMED CT"
msgstr "SNOMED CT"

# Provides a complete explanation of the meaning of the data element for human readability.  For the case of elements derived from existing elements (e.g. constraints), the definition SHALL be consistent with the base definition, but convey the meaning of the element in the particular context of use of the resource. (Note: The text you are reading is specified in ElementDefinition.definition).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Condition.code.coding:SCT/definition
msgid "SNOMED CT er ei systematisk samling av helsefaglege omgrep som kan brukast til å dokumentere og dele opplysningar knytt til pasientbehandlinga. Ved å bruke eit felles omgrepsapparat skal det bli lettare å kommunisere mellom ulike delar av helsetenesta."
msgstr "SNOMED CT is a systematic collection of clinical concepts that can be used to document and share information related to patient care. Using a common terminology makes it easier to communicate across different parts of the health service."

